## sons types
Bats have been using echolocation for millions of years to navigate in the dark. They regularly emit **"sonar"** type sounds to scan their immediate environment and "see" any obstacles or insects in the air. However, they are not blind and their sense of sight is secondary.
Other sounds are used for communication with their fellow bats, either in their roosts (such as between mother and offspring) where they are longer and lower in frequency, or when interacting with each other in flight over a hunting ground. These are known as **social calls**.
[![Bat social calls](https://i.giphy.com/media/v1.Y2lkPTc5MGI3NjExbmsyYjJ6d3FqNWVveGo5eTBiaDQwM2p1MzFzYm54d3h0cnA0NXg0eSZlcD12MV9pbnRlcm5hbF9naWZfYnlfaWQmY3Q9Zw/fU5k7LCUBUBs9Y3ptM/giphy.gif)](https://youtube.com/shorts/eA_8P5fo5NI?feature=share) _Guillaume  Marchais_
Finally, a captured animal will emit distress calls that are almost audible to humans.

