## sons type 3
* **Constant frequency or CF** : calls looking like an horizontal axis : the Greater horseshoe bats
[![Grand rhinolophe](https://media.giphy.com/media/v1.Y2lkPTc5MGI3NjExbTFrc2NnbjVlcWU5ZzV1NGRoeXZwOXlrdGk5bWo3Nmx0N3M1bmk3eCZlcD12MV9pbnRlcm5hbF9naWZfYnlfaWQmY3Q9Zw/aGnJDGVuknjzaOhHmr/giphy.gif)](https://youtube.com/shorts/yqe4rqG5m2M) _Guillaume  Marchais (Echo Meter Touch 2)_
* **Frequency-modulated or FM** : calls looking like a vertical axis : the Natterer's bat [![Murin de Natterer chasse - expansion x10](https://media.giphy.com/media/v1.Y2lkPTc5MGI3NjExeDc3MDRybTNhYTNuNmx5eXByZndrc3RwemhidzE5Ynd5b3NuZDJrbSZlcD12MV9pbnRlcm5hbF9naWZfYnlfaWQmY3Q9Zw/wRrkRVlDZNaTXc3sCN/giphy.gif)](https://youtube.com/shorts/s3tleMoh92w) _Guillaume  Marchais (Echo Meter Touch 2)_
* **A mixture of both FM-CF** : calls looking like a vertical axis to start with but ending with an horizontal tail containing the maximum of energy: the [Common pipistrelle and the Savi's bat](https://youtu.be/ggtdqT4K_1o?feature=shared) 

