## esp commune
- common species
- common pipistrelle
- common serotine
- Daubenton's bat
- Natterer's bat
The other species can roughly be divided into two categories: those most commonly and least frequently detected.
* **Common pipistrelle**: the most frequently encountered species in general
[![Common pipistrelle hunting - expansion x10](https://media.giphy.com/media/v1.Y2lkPTc5MGI3NjExeXg5M3RyMGs0M2VvNXhobGhzYjUyYzFuMjZoNHR3OXd4bHhhMHdkbSZlcD12MV9pbnRlcm5hbF9naWZfYnlfaWQmY3Q9Zw/XLhD3IR0osg6P1dItj/giphy.gif)](https://youtube.com/shorts/fpqj9ydZM4Y) _Guillaume Marchais (Echo Meter Touch 2)_
* **Common serotine** *: a large species that hunts at the edge and often roosts in attics
[![Common serotine hunting - expansion x10](https://media.giphy.com/media/v1.Y2lkPTc5MGI3NjExd3lrMTk1NXBzYWJ0YmNsMmJ5cDRhb3dkM2p4Zmc2cDNya2NoN3oxYyZlcD12MV9pbnRlcm5hbF9naWZfYnlfaWQmY3Q9Zw/IrNhlVXmcb4R9uTBW2/giphy.gif)](https://youtube.com/shorts/8FmeJPnSOY4) _Guillaume Marchais (Echo Meter Touch 2)_
* **Daubenton's bat**: a species often encountered above lakes and waterways.
[![Daubenton's bat hunting - expansion x10](https://media.giphy.com/media/v1.Y2lkPTc5MGI3NjExaGdpdjA5eHdpYmN3ejAxOWRid2c4eHg3bXB0ZTV4MHRxd2NlNHJ4cCZlcD12MV9pbnRlcm5hbF9naWZfYnlfaWQmY3Q9Zw/rinkzjbBYH89MCTFsI/giphy.gif)](https://youtube.com/shorts/ovts9Ez3KLk) _Guillaume Marchais (Echo Meter Touch 2)_
* **Natterer's bat**: a species often encountered in various rural areas
[![Natterer's bat hunting - expansion x10](https://media.giphy.com/media/v1.Y2lkPTc5MGI3NjExeDc3MDRybTNhYTNuNmx5eXByZndrc3RwemhidzE5Ynd5b3NuZDJrbSZlcD12MV9pbnRlcm5hbF9naWZfYnlfaWQmY3Q9Zw/wRrkRVlDZNaTXc3sCN/giphy.gif)](https://youtube.com/shorts/s3tleMoh92w) _Guillaume Marchais (Echo Meter Touch 2)_

