## analyse ordi
- software
- computer
- training
Certain species require advanced learning to allow for species discrimination as much as possible within the limits of recording quality and signal quantity.
Specialized books, guides, and tutorials allow for self-learning to some extent.
Here is a non-exhaustive list of sources:
BOOKS
- [BARATAUD, M. 2020. Acoustic ecology of European bats. Species Identification, Studies of Their Habitats and Foraging Behaviour. 2d ed. Biotope, Mèze; Muséum national d’histoire naturelle, Paris (Inventaires et biodiversité Series), 352 p.](http://geoeco.fr/ecologie_acoustique/en/index.html)
- [RUSS J., 2021. Bat Calls of Britain and Europe. Pelagic publishing, 462 p. ](https://pelagicpublishing.com/products/bat-calls-of-britain-and-europe-russ-pelagic-9781784272258)
- [MIDDLETON N., FROUD A., FRENCH K. 2022  Social Calls of the Bats of Britain and Ireland, 2nd., Pelagic publishig, 300 p.](https://pelagicpublishing.com/products/social-calls-of-the-bats-of-britain-and-ireland-2nd-edn)
ONLINE DOCS
- [Bayerische Landesamt für Umwelt, 2020. Analysis of Bat Call Recordings and Criteria for the Evaluation of Acoustic Identification of Species. Translation : David Lee](https://batability.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Analysis-of-Batcalls-1.pdf)
- [MIDDLETON N., 2020. Analysis of Analook files - Tutorial, 23 p.](https://batability.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/AnaLook-Analysis-Screen-Grab-Tutorial.pdf)

And a list of free software packages:
- [Kaleidoscope Lite](https://www.wildlifeacoustics.com/products/kaleidoscope/kaleidoscope-lite) : allows you to "manipulate" raw files and convert them to different formats (WAV; ZC ; W4C)
- [AnalookW](https://users.lmi.net/corben/WinAnalook.htm#AnaLookW_Contents) : only allows analysis of lightweight ZC files with poor resolution. Useful for large volumes to process. [Video tutorials](https://youtu.be/FSVgMu8JOOc) by Guillaume Marchais explain the different steps of processing.
- [Chirosurf](https://vigie-chiro.forumactif.com/t108-chirosurf-2-2-analyse-bioacoustique-gratuit-portable-01-01-24) : allows you to learn how to dissect a recorded file in time expansion format WAV (French only)

In Europe, the [BTO Acoustic Pipeline](https://www.bto.org/our-science/products-and-technologies/bto-acoustic-pipeline) provides tools for the detection and identification of birds, bats and other wildlife in both audible and ultrasonic sound recordings.
In France, the [VIGIECHIROS national participatory science program](https://www.vigienature.fr/fr/page/participer-vigie-chiro) offers all participants the opportunity to upload or upload their recordings for automated analysis by their TADARIDA classifier.

Other advanced software solutions are available for purchase as an annual or permanent license:
- Sonochiro from Biotope (Europe and Overseas)
- Kaleidoscope pro from Wildlife Acoustics (International)
- Sonobat (North America)

